<p>
<lb n="1"/><note n="77-3">The beginning which must have been on the previous face of the stone</note>guḍivāḍa
<lb n="2" break="no"/>Aṁdu Āgnēya
<lb n="3" break="no"/>mu dikkuna ve
<lb n="4" break="no"/>ḍlapu 12 niḍupu
<lb n="5"/>25 mūḍlu vīniṁ
<lb n="6"/>jēkoni golla sūrebō
<lb n="7" break="no"/>yuni Ā brahmana
<lb n="8" break="no"/>bōyuni koḍkulu dē
<lb n="9" break="no"/>vanabhōyuṁḍunu bra
<lb n="10" break="no"/>mmanabōyuṁḍunu
<lb n="11"/>naṁdimānika nitya māne
<lb n="12" break="no"/>ḍu neI Ācaṁdrārkkamu naḍa
<lb n="13" break="no"/>paṁgalavāru <g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g> Ā malle
<lb n="14" break="no"/>bōyuni peddakoḍku pāri
<lb n="15" break="no"/>senabōyuṁḍu guḍivā
<lb n="16" break="no"/>ḍa kuṁdēśvaraśrīmahādēva
<lb n="17" break="no"/>raku niccina Aṁgaḍisuṁka
<lb n="18" break="no"/>mu Ēmi sarakamminānu mā
<lb n="19" break="no"/>ḍavīsāmu lekkanu veli nye
<lb n="20" break="no"/>vahārulu veṭṭuvāru <supplied reason="undefined"><g ref="sym:bar" type="punctuation">.</g></supplied> kōma
<lb n="21" break="no"/>ṭi peṁḍlini kūṁttuvāru rūka Accuvāru <g ref="sym:doubleBar" type="punctuation">.</g>
